WEBVTT

00:01.262 --> 00:04.004
I know what I want,
and I want you.

00:04.047 --> 00:05.179
I want someone
who doesn't need to take weeks

00:05.222 --> 00:07.050
to figure out
if they wanna be with me.

00:08.051 --> 00:09.226
MARIANA:
Who is that guy?

00:09.270 --> 00:12.795
Joaquin. He is
our newest Coterie member.

00:12.838 --> 00:15.537
MARIANA: Do you always
answer a question
by asking another question?

00:15.580 --> 00:16.712
CALLIE: What do you think
of the new guy?

00:16.755 --> 00:18.061
I think he's a dick.

00:18.105 --> 00:19.323
This is Stef and Lena.

00:19.367 --> 00:21.064
-LENA: Hi, Ka'Maya.
-STEF: Hi there.

00:21.108 --> 00:23.414
I killed Zack.

00:23.458 --> 00:25.851
I didn't mean to
but I killed him.

00:25.895 --> 00:27.462
CALLIE:
If you don't help Kathleen,

00:27.505 --> 00:29.116
I'll send this
to Zack's family.

00:29.159 --> 00:31.074
He'll be branded a murderer.

00:31.118 --> 00:33.598
Kinda seems like
the universe keeps
pushing us together.

00:33.642 --> 00:34.991
CALLIE:
I've been thinking

00:35.035 --> 00:36.601
like of this is
as good as it gets.

00:37.472 --> 00:38.995
Maybe it's not.

00:39.039 --> 00:42.085
I need to make
some big life changes.

00:43.130 --> 00:45.697
♪

01:06.283 --> 01:08.416
[whimsical music]

01:08.459 --> 01:11.375
♪

01:39.316 --> 01:43.059
♪ Pa-pa-pa
Pa-pa-pa-pa-pa ♪

01:43.103 --> 01:46.715
♪ Pa-pa-pa
Pa-pa-pa-pa-pa ♪

01:46.758 --> 01:51.198
♪ Then we'll find
our peace of mind ♪

01:51.241 --> 01:53.722
♪ You and me, Bel Ami

01:53.765 --> 01:59.119
♪ Pa-pa-pa, pa-paaa

01:59.162 --> 02:01.033
Ka'Maya,
are you hungry?

02:01.077 --> 02:02.687
Ooh, how about
some peanut butter
and apples?

02:02.731 --> 02:04.776
LENA:
Yum, great idea.

02:04.820 --> 02:06.169
You know, that was
Mariana's favorite
when she was little.

02:06.213 --> 02:08.476
Oh, you know what?
She doesn't like peanut butter.

02:08.519 --> 02:09.738
What? Since when?

02:09.781 --> 02:11.914
Uh, well, it's been a while.
Right?

02:11.957 --> 02:14.699
It makes
my tongue sticky.

02:14.743 --> 02:16.875
STEF: She does like
the sunflower seed butter,
if you have that.

02:16.919 --> 02:17.920
I know it's really
kind of specific.

02:17.963 --> 02:21.053
Uh, let me see.

02:21.097 --> 02:22.533
Looks like you're in luck,

02:22.577 --> 02:25.188
although I don't know
how long it's been in here.

02:25.232 --> 02:26.320
Just check the date.

02:27.234 --> 02:28.148
It's on the bottom.

02:30.672 --> 02:33.631
Uh, Moms, this is Joaquin.
He just moved in.

02:33.675 --> 02:35.198
Hi, very nice to meet you.

02:35.242 --> 02:37.983
Hi, nice to meet you.
I'm Stef. This is Lena.

02:38.027 --> 02:40.247
And Ka'Maya
is our foster sister.

02:40.290 --> 02:41.161
Where are you guys
visiting from?

02:41.204 --> 02:42.553
San Diego.

02:42.597 --> 02:43.902
Oh, it's really nice
down there.

02:43.946 --> 02:45.252
You just up here to visit?

02:48.037 --> 02:49.691
So how do you think
this is going to go down?

02:49.734 --> 02:51.562
Like a lead balloon.

02:51.606 --> 02:53.912
Which is why I'm glad
we're dropping the news
as a family.

02:53.956 --> 02:55.697
What's a lead balloon?

02:55.740 --> 02:58.700
You know what,
it is a very, very,
very heavy balloon...

03:00.397 --> 03:01.572
filled with bad news.

03:01.616 --> 03:03.792
It's not bad news.

03:03.835 --> 03:05.228
Yeah,
we are just visiting.

03:05.272 --> 03:06.403
Haven't seen the girls
in a while

03:06.447 --> 03:08.971
and had no plans
for the weekend, so...

03:09.014 --> 03:11.539
We were supposed
to go to Disneyland.

03:11.582 --> 03:12.757
I know, but we can
go to Disneyland...

03:12.801 --> 03:14.846
-[phone buzzing]
-...whenever we want to.

03:14.890 --> 03:17.849
And Mama had a...
She had a free weekend.

03:17.893 --> 03:19.460
Apparently not.

03:19.503 --> 03:20.591
There's an important vote
on the floor today.

03:20.635 --> 03:21.984
I've got to take this.

03:22.027 --> 03:23.594
STEF:
So much for a rare weekend.

03:25.814 --> 03:27.337
It seems like
I wasn't the only one

03:27.381 --> 03:29.992
who had other plans
this weekend.

03:30.035 --> 03:31.515
I wonder what the sudden visit
is all about.

03:32.951 --> 03:35.476
I think it's great.
We hardly see them.

03:35.519 --> 03:38.000
I know, but I wasn't up
for a last-minute surprise.

03:38.043 --> 03:39.567
I have a lot
to do this weekend.

03:39.610 --> 03:41.133
[elevator bell dings]

03:42.874 --> 03:45.094
Hey!
Oh, I'm so happy

03:45.137 --> 03:46.008
that you came up
this weekend.

03:46.051 --> 03:47.966
What a nice surprise.

03:48.010 --> 03:51.143
-Hi.
-Hi.

03:51.187 --> 03:53.885
So do you guys get up here
much to visit or...

03:53.929 --> 03:55.278
Um, we've been up here
a couple of times

03:55.322 --> 03:56.888
since the girls
moved in here.

03:56.932 --> 03:59.021
Nice. When was that?

03:59.064 --> 04:01.545
Uh, about
11 months ago now.

04:02.677 --> 04:03.939
Hey.

04:03.982 --> 04:05.114
-Hey, Dennis.
-This is a nice surprise.

04:05.157 --> 04:07.421
Yes, a last-minute one.

04:07.464 --> 04:08.813
-Good to see you, Dennis.
-Good to see you too.

04:08.857 --> 04:11.468
-How you've been?
-Um, this is Ka'Maya.

04:11.512 --> 04:13.688
And, uh, Moms,
have you met Isabella?

04:13.731 --> 04:15.124
-No.
-No.

04:15.167 --> 04:16.560
We haven't.
Nice to meet you.

04:16.604 --> 04:18.258
Thank you.
Um, you too.

04:18.301 --> 04:20.303
Uh, I thought that
you had moved out.

04:20.347 --> 04:22.392
-I, um, I--
-She's back.

04:22.436 --> 04:23.741
Oh.

04:23.785 --> 04:25.613
And yes,
she's pregnant.

04:25.656 --> 04:27.310
-Mm-hmm.
-Congratulations!

04:27.354 --> 04:29.704
Yes. Congratulations
to the both of you.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.619
Oh, no, no, no.
He's not the father.

04:31.662 --> 04:32.446
He is.

04:36.058 --> 04:38.930
Oh! Gael's the father.

04:38.974 --> 04:41.019
Hey! Nice to see
you guys again.

04:41.063 --> 04:42.325
Great to see you again.

04:42.369 --> 04:45.285
Um, so where do we
wanna go for dinner tonight?

04:45.328 --> 04:49.027
Oh, there's a really cute
kids' friendly pizza place
around the corner.

04:49.071 --> 04:51.813
Uh, well, we thought
that it might be fun

04:51.856 --> 04:54.990
to have a-- a grownup dinner.

04:55.033 --> 04:57.122
Oh, um, I'd be happy
to watch Ka'Maya

04:57.166 --> 04:58.515
while you guys go out.

04:58.559 --> 05:00.604
I used to do
princess parties,

05:00.648 --> 05:02.693
so I'm really good
at entertaining kids.

05:02.737 --> 05:05.827
-I want a princess party.
-You do?

05:05.870 --> 05:07.872
Oh, thank you.
That would be really great.

05:07.916 --> 05:09.744
-Thank you.
-That's okay.

05:09.787 --> 05:11.093
What?

05:11.136 --> 05:12.703
Well, we've never
left her before.

05:12.747 --> 05:15.097
You leave her when you go
to Sacramento all the time.

05:15.140 --> 05:16.925
-What are you talking about?
-With you.

05:16.968 --> 05:19.319
Well, I just-- I thought we were
gonna have a grownup dinner

05:19.362 --> 05:22.060
with a grownup
conversation tonight maybe.

05:22.104 --> 05:23.497
DENNIS: Well,
if you want to stay in,

05:23.540 --> 05:25.455
we were gonna
cook dinner tonight.

05:25.499 --> 05:27.239
JOAQUIN: Oh, is this like
one of those family dinners

05:27.283 --> 05:28.632
I keep hearing
so much about?

05:28.676 --> 05:29.807
We're having
a family dinner?

05:29.851 --> 05:32.332
Oh, my God! Hi!

05:32.375 --> 05:33.463
It's so lovely
to see you guys.

05:33.507 --> 05:36.074
Hey! I thought
I heard y'all.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.294
DAVIA: We're having
a family dinner!

05:38.338 --> 05:39.339
Uh, well...

05:39.382 --> 05:41.732
And you must be Ka'Maya.

05:41.776 --> 05:44.213
I have heard
so much about you.

05:44.256 --> 05:45.736
All right,
so it's settled then.

05:45.780 --> 05:48.565
Yes. We can have
a grownup conversation
afterwards.

05:48.609 --> 05:50.393
STEF:
I'll help make something.

05:50.437 --> 05:53.744
Um, yeah.
Yeah, sounds good. Why not?

05:53.788 --> 05:56.399
I will just let Jude know
that we're staying in.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.358
Great.

06:03.232 --> 06:05.060
♪

06:06.540 --> 06:07.845
[indistinct chatter]

06:09.804 --> 06:11.545
Hey, why are you buried
in your phone, sir?

06:11.588 --> 06:12.763
It's a party. Come on!

06:12.807 --> 06:14.548
I think Carter and I
might be in a fight.

06:14.591 --> 06:16.637
[phone buzzes]

06:16.680 --> 06:18.595
Great! I just asked
if we could talk later,

06:18.639 --> 06:20.554
and he texted, "Sure."

06:20.597 --> 06:22.033
-Oh, no.
-What's wrong with that?

06:22.077 --> 06:23.426
What does that mean?

06:23.470 --> 06:25.428
Like, "Sure, whatever,"

06:25.472 --> 06:27.082
or "Sure,
looking forward to it"?

06:27.125 --> 06:29.040
Long-distance relationships
suck.

06:29.084 --> 06:30.346
JOAQUIN:
More wine?

06:30.390 --> 06:32.435
-Yes, please.
-JOAQUIN: All right.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.568
Hey, how's Ka'Maya doing?

06:34.611 --> 06:35.830
Passed out.

06:35.873 --> 06:37.701
-Here, let me get you a glass.
-Thank you.

06:39.834 --> 06:43.751
So what is this
grownup conversation all about?

06:50.497 --> 06:52.629
Ken Sung convinced his sister

06:52.673 --> 06:54.805
to give the FBI
enough information

06:54.849 --> 06:56.459
to put her husband away,

06:56.503 --> 07:01.595
and in return,
the FBI agreed to drop

07:01.638 --> 07:03.814
any investigations
into my old books.

07:03.858 --> 07:05.033
Congratulations.

07:06.426 --> 07:08.515
Well, I owe it all to you.

07:08.558 --> 07:10.865
The question is

07:10.908 --> 07:14.172
how did you get
Ken Sung to change his mind?

07:17.524 --> 07:19.308
I appealed
to his conscience.

07:22.442 --> 07:26.533
Hmm. Wow, I'm impressed.

07:26.576 --> 07:29.057
I might turn you
into a mini-me after all.

07:29.100 --> 07:30.188
[Kathleen chuckles]

07:31.494 --> 07:33.583
So what is our next case?

07:33.627 --> 07:35.542
I'm thinking
a wrongful conviction

07:35.585 --> 07:36.630
might be interesting.

07:46.988 --> 07:49.512
Well, looks like I made it
just in time for dinner.

07:50.165 --> 07:51.471
I'm kidding.

07:52.820 --> 07:56.040
Um, these are my moms,
Stef and Lena.

07:56.084 --> 07:57.389
This is Kathleen.

07:57.433 --> 07:59.522
-Oh.
-Oh.

07:59.566 --> 08:01.132
Uh, we've heard
a lot about you.

08:01.176 --> 08:03.308
Hmm. None of it good,
I assume.

08:05.354 --> 08:07.051
-Hi, Mariana.
-Hi.

08:07.095 --> 08:10.315
I believe that
these belong to you.

08:10.359 --> 08:11.752
-I washed them.
-Thank you.

08:13.101 --> 08:15.495
I am sorry to drop by
unannounced,

08:15.538 --> 08:17.366
but I was in the neighborhood.

08:17.409 --> 08:19.673
Not at all. Um...
Why don't we go into my loft?

08:19.716 --> 08:21.326
Oh, Ka'Maya
is sleeping in there.

08:22.197 --> 08:23.503
Uh, okay.

08:23.546 --> 08:26.854
Uh, Malika, can we,
um, talk in your loft?

08:26.897 --> 08:28.029
Yeah, of course.

08:29.683 --> 08:30.814
Well, it was nice
to meet you.

08:32.337 --> 08:35.384
You did a great job
with both your daughters.

08:35.427 --> 08:36.690
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

08:38.735 --> 08:40.258
I wonder
what that's all about.

08:42.957 --> 08:45.046
Does it need more tarragon?
Is that enough?

08:45.089 --> 08:46.221
I don't think so.

08:49.659 --> 08:51.487
-Oh, excuse me.
-Excuse me.

08:53.707 --> 08:55.012
Are you okay with us?

08:55.056 --> 08:56.144
Do me a favor.

08:56.187 --> 08:58.581
-Stop asking me if we're okay.
-Okay.

08:58.625 --> 09:01.453
And listen, if you wanna invite
Matt over for dinner, I'm cool.

09:01.497 --> 09:02.716
He's a really nice guy.

09:02.759 --> 09:04.718
No. Yeah, I mean, uh,

09:04.761 --> 09:06.589
he already
had plans tonight, so...

09:06.633 --> 09:07.547
Thank you.

09:14.989 --> 09:16.207
Can I talk to you
in my loft?

09:21.473 --> 09:23.258
Hey. What's wrong?

09:23.301 --> 09:25.956
-Matt dumped me.
-What? Why?

09:26.000 --> 09:27.828
He said he wanted someone
who didn't take weeks

09:27.871 --> 09:30.221
to figure out
that they wanted him.

09:30.265 --> 09:32.789
Also, he thinks I'm still
in love with Dennis.

09:32.833 --> 09:33.703
Come here.

09:36.837 --> 09:38.578
So, why didn't
you tell me?

09:38.621 --> 09:41.189
Well, I didn't
tell anyone.

09:41.232 --> 09:42.364
I'm just so embarrassed,
you know?

09:42.407 --> 09:43.495
I mean, here I thought
I was gonna have

09:43.539 --> 09:45.759
this great
romantic moment with Matt.

09:45.802 --> 09:48.109
And then he just rips the rug
right out from under me.

09:48.152 --> 09:49.458
Davia, I'm so sorry.

09:49.501 --> 09:50.415
Why do men suck?

09:51.199 --> 09:52.374
Yeah, I don't know.

09:52.417 --> 09:55.856
I just--
I needed to tell someone.

09:55.899 --> 09:58.641
But please don't tell
anyone else, especially Dennis,

09:58.685 --> 10:01.252
for reasons I'm not
100% clear on yet.

10:02.123 --> 10:03.603
-Okay?
-Yeah, okay.

10:06.083 --> 10:09.086
[loud cheering and laughing]

10:14.265 --> 10:16.441
Oh, my God!
What are you doing here?

10:16.485 --> 10:17.921
ALICE:
I had a couple days
off the tour

10:17.965 --> 10:20.054
and I thought
I'd surprise everyone!

10:20.097 --> 10:21.359
Look here,
we got company.

10:26.016 --> 10:27.670
I know
what's going on.

10:27.714 --> 10:29.193
You do?

10:29.237 --> 10:30.760
I know why
the sudden visit.

10:31.892 --> 10:34.111
Moms are
adopting Ka'Maya.

10:34.155 --> 10:35.722
That's what
they came down to tell us.

10:35.765 --> 10:37.549
I don't know why
they're acting so cagey
about it, though.

10:37.593 --> 10:39.551
-Am I right?
-I don't know, maybe.

10:43.860 --> 10:46.254
STEF:
Well, this is absolutely
delicious, thank you.

10:46.297 --> 10:48.604
I agree. Our compliments
to the chef.

10:48.648 --> 10:50.780
-To Dennis and Isabella.
-Hear! Hear!

10:50.824 --> 10:52.826
I didn't do much.
Dennis is the culinary genius.

10:52.869 --> 10:54.741
Don't sell yourself short.

10:54.784 --> 10:58.222
A chef is nothing
without his sous chef.

10:58.266 --> 11:01.530
How-- So how's it, uh,
on the road with Margaret Cho?

11:01.573 --> 11:03.837
A dream come true.
I'm still processing.

11:03.880 --> 11:06.100
Yeah, I can't believe it.
Epic.

11:06.143 --> 11:07.928
Malika, how's
the transition been

11:07.971 --> 11:09.581
from activism to politics?

11:09.625 --> 11:12.454
Hmm, feels
too soon to tell.

11:12.497 --> 11:14.151
But how's it going
in the state assembly?

11:14.195 --> 11:16.153
Well, even being
in the majority,

11:16.197 --> 11:18.503
getting things done
is still an uphill battle.

11:18.547 --> 11:21.898
Well, the governor just approved
a bill that Lena coauthored

11:21.942 --> 11:23.683
to shift certain
emergency response calls

11:23.726 --> 11:25.075
from law enforcement

11:25.119 --> 11:27.338
to trained mental health
professionals.

11:27.382 --> 11:29.036
So important.
Congratulations.

11:29.079 --> 11:30.690
JOAQUIN: Just, uh...
Just curious.

11:30.733 --> 11:33.693
Where do you stand
on the whole
defunding police?

11:33.736 --> 11:36.565
I... think
it's up to the cities.

11:36.608 --> 11:37.740
They control the budgets.

11:37.784 --> 11:41.048
Hmm. Kind of dodged
the question there.

11:41.091 --> 11:43.050
MARIANA:
Joaquin is a journalist.

11:43.093 --> 11:45.443
Just in case you're wondering
why everything feels
like an interrogation.

11:45.487 --> 11:48.403
Yeah, I just-- I don't believe
there are any good cops.

11:48.446 --> 11:50.753
Not as long as they put blue
before duty, you know?

11:50.797 --> 11:51.928
My mom Stef was a cop.

11:53.103 --> 11:54.191
Oh.

11:54.235 --> 11:55.236
STEF: And while
I strongly disagree

11:55.279 --> 11:57.107
that there
are no good cops, um,

11:57.151 --> 11:59.544
I have seen
the issues firsthand.

11:59.588 --> 12:02.765
We definitely need reform,
but I do not believe

12:02.809 --> 12:06.160
that it's, uh, it's possible
to abolish police entirely.

12:06.203 --> 12:07.465
Why not?

12:07.509 --> 12:08.684
LENA: You know,
most of my voters,

12:08.728 --> 12:10.207
they hear,
"Defund the police,"

12:10.251 --> 12:12.514
and they're scared off
any conversation about reform.

12:12.557 --> 12:15.517
Well, people found
Black Lives Matter
too confronting at first.

12:15.560 --> 12:17.867
Sometimes you just got
to take a bold stance, you know?

12:17.911 --> 12:19.086
-Get people to talk.
-I agree.

12:19.129 --> 12:21.131
Heavy.

12:21.175 --> 12:23.220
This is why I try to avoid
these family dinners.

12:23.264 --> 12:24.308
Fair enough.
Fair enough.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.659
-JUDE: Great.
-What?

12:27.703 --> 12:28.965
Carter's going to sleep.

12:29.009 --> 12:31.011
So now he wants to talk
in the morning.

12:31.054 --> 12:33.448
Sweetheart, please
put away the phone.
We're at dinner--

12:33.491 --> 12:35.015
-I hate texting.
-STEF: Well, then don't.

12:35.058 --> 12:36.712
I mean, how do you read
anyone's tone?

12:36.756 --> 12:39.323
I agree. You have to put
an exclamation point
after everything,

12:39.367 --> 12:40.803
so people don't
take it the wrong way.

12:40.847 --> 12:42.805
Yeah! And what about
a thumbs up?

12:42.849 --> 12:45.199
Personally, I've always read
that as complacent.

12:45.242 --> 12:47.201
And everyone
loves everything.

12:47.244 --> 12:49.420
I mean, why are people
more effusive over texts

12:49.464 --> 12:50.770
than in person?

12:50.813 --> 12:53.076
Okay, see, this is why
I'm all about the emoji.

12:53.120 --> 12:56.776
[overlapping chatter]

12:56.819 --> 12:58.821
Jude, seriously,
off the phone, please.

12:58.865 --> 13:00.736
Come on, you can talk
to Carter in the morning.

13:00.780 --> 13:01.955
What is the big deal?

13:01.998 --> 13:03.957
You do know
"talk" means sex?

13:04.000 --> 13:05.219
-Ew.
-STEF: Since when?
That's disgusting.

13:05.262 --> 13:07.351
You do know
that we're your family?

13:07.395 --> 13:08.744
And I don't think
anyone else

13:08.788 --> 13:11.312
cares to imagine you sexting
with your boyfriend.

13:11.355 --> 13:13.053
That's another issue.

13:13.096 --> 13:15.098
He likes to sext,
and I prefer vidsex.

13:15.142 --> 13:17.535
KELLY:
Oh, so he's old school.
I dig it.

13:17.579 --> 13:19.015
Sexting can be fun.

13:19.059 --> 13:20.364
MARIANA and CALLIE:
Mama!

13:20.408 --> 13:22.758
STEF: What? Mama
is a great sexter.

13:22.802 --> 13:25.152
-Mom!
-Very vivid visuals.

13:25.195 --> 13:27.589
She knows all the...
What do they call the...

13:27.632 --> 13:29.330
Woah, woah, woah.
Let them speak.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.332
Yeah, say more, please.

13:31.375 --> 13:33.813
[all cheering]

13:33.856 --> 13:35.336
CALLIE: Enough.
Okay, okay, okay.

13:35.379 --> 13:37.773
Jude, stop reading
into Carter's text

13:37.817 --> 13:39.340
and just stop playing games,
all right?

13:39.383 --> 13:40.950
Just be honest with him.

13:40.994 --> 13:43.083
Okay, then why don't we all
just be honest with Mariana?

13:48.392 --> 13:49.829
What? Honest about what?

13:51.874 --> 13:53.702
Okay, what's going on?

13:53.745 --> 13:54.921
I know you two
didn't just come up here

13:54.964 --> 13:56.618
because you miss us.

13:56.661 --> 13:58.054
You're adopting
Ka'Maya, right?

13:59.099 --> 13:59.969
Uh, mmm...

14:01.057 --> 14:03.886
Well, while we would love to,

14:03.930 --> 14:06.323
no, that is not the reason
that we came up here.

14:08.195 --> 14:09.457
Okay, well then, do you know?

14:09.500 --> 14:12.068
Because you must,
they keep looking at you.

14:12.112 --> 14:12.808
What's going on?

14:16.116 --> 14:18.858
-I got a job with the ACLU.
-MARIANA: What?

14:18.901 --> 14:20.729
[all exclaiming]

14:22.339 --> 14:24.559
Okay, that's great.
That's your dream job.

14:24.602 --> 14:25.777
What's the big deal?

14:26.778 --> 14:27.823
In Washington, D.C.

14:29.172 --> 14:30.913
MALIKA:
Okay!

14:30.957 --> 14:33.785
Oh, in Washington, D.C.?

14:34.482 --> 14:35.526
Yeah.

14:37.180 --> 14:39.617
Okay, so you're moving?

14:43.099 --> 14:44.318
When do you leave?

14:45.275 --> 14:46.537
In two days.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.941
Like a lead balloon.

14:58.985 --> 15:00.987
Ka'Maya is asleep.

15:01.030 --> 15:03.728
Okay. This family dinner
finally got interesting.

15:16.219 --> 15:17.133
[closes door]

15:19.179 --> 15:20.136
Hey.

15:22.660 --> 15:23.748
Two days?

15:25.054 --> 15:27.187
Seriously, you're leaving
in two days?

15:27.230 --> 15:29.319
Ho-- How did this
even happen?

15:31.669 --> 15:34.020
So what is our next case?

15:34.063 --> 15:35.847
I'm thinking
a wrongful conviction

15:35.891 --> 15:37.023
might be interesting.

15:48.904 --> 15:52.299
Do I at least
get a two-week notice?

15:55.867 --> 15:56.956
I'm sorry.

15:59.480 --> 16:02.396
This just isn't
the right job for me.

16:04.224 --> 16:06.313
I know.

16:06.356 --> 16:09.751
You're a crusader, Callie,
in search of a crusade.

16:09.794 --> 16:13.407
I just lost sight of why
I wanted to become a lawyer.

16:13.450 --> 16:16.976
You know? What I really want
to do is work for the ACLU.

16:19.413 --> 16:20.370
Well...

16:22.590 --> 16:24.984
I happen to know
the executive director

16:25.767 --> 16:27.812
of the ACLU in D.C.

16:29.423 --> 16:30.815
If you're willing to move,

16:32.382 --> 16:33.818
I can make a call.

16:36.082 --> 16:37.518
I'm sorry.

16:37.561 --> 16:39.259
Kathleen made a call,

16:39.302 --> 16:40.956
and it all happened
so fast,

16:41.000 --> 16:42.349
and I knew
that you'd be upset,

16:42.392 --> 16:44.394
so I wanted Moms and Jude

16:44.438 --> 16:46.744
to come and help
break the news.

16:49.312 --> 16:50.226
Well, you're right.

16:51.401 --> 16:52.185
I am upset.

16:54.404 --> 16:57.233
But not that
you got your dream job

16:57.277 --> 16:59.192
or that you're moving
across the country.

17:02.151 --> 17:04.675
I'm upset that you thought
I was so fragile

17:04.719 --> 17:06.503
that you couldn't just
tell me yourself.

17:08.592 --> 17:11.030
And now I have no time
to throw you a going-away party.

17:13.728 --> 17:16.513
Well, there's no time
like the present.

17:21.127 --> 17:23.085
To my sister

17:23.129 --> 17:24.478
changing the world.

17:24.521 --> 17:27.220
[all cheering]

17:29.048 --> 17:32.051
♪

17:40.102 --> 17:41.538
[phone chimes]

17:43.279 --> 17:46.456
I just added you to
the Coterie Biatches
group chat.

17:46.500 --> 17:49.068
-Finally.
-Better late than never.

17:49.111 --> 17:51.461
Of course, now we can't talk
about you anymore.

17:53.333 --> 17:55.117
[both laugh]

17:55.161 --> 17:57.206
We're seriously
gonna miss you.

17:57.250 --> 17:58.338
I'm gonna miss you too.

18:00.557 --> 18:03.212
Aw. I almost believed you.

18:04.474 --> 18:06.650
Yo.

18:06.694 --> 18:09.392
This is like
my second Coterie party
since I moved in.

18:09.436 --> 18:11.351
Is it always like this?

18:11.394 --> 18:14.136
Well, when I first moved in,
it was a party every night,

18:14.180 --> 18:16.573
but... things have mellowed.

18:16.617 --> 18:17.444
Nice.

18:18.749 --> 18:20.142
When was that?

18:20.186 --> 18:21.056
When did
you first move in?

18:22.492 --> 18:23.667
To Callie

18:23.711 --> 18:24.842
rocking D.C.!

18:24.886 --> 18:26.583
[all cheering]

18:35.592 --> 18:37.594
Although I've never
really gotten you at all,

18:37.638 --> 18:40.249
I have grown accustomed
to your superior attitude

18:40.293 --> 18:41.990
and your
White Shoulders perfume.

18:42.033 --> 18:43.078
I don't wear perfume.

18:43.774 --> 18:45.602
Huh.

18:45.646 --> 18:47.996
Well, you smell
like an old lady.

18:48.039 --> 18:51.826
And even though
I hate goodbyes,

18:51.869 --> 18:54.089
I really am going to miss
trying to avoid you
around here.

18:56.657 --> 18:58.920
["Don't Waste My Time"
by Cy Dune playing]

18:58.963 --> 19:04.273
♪ I won'’t waste
your time, time, time no more ♪

19:04.317 --> 19:07.407
♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na, na
Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

19:11.498 --> 19:13.500
I can't believe
I stole your ID

19:13.543 --> 19:16.503
to get into
Judge Wilson's office.

19:16.546 --> 19:19.375
Oh, I can't believe I missed
you reading him the Riot Act.

19:19.419 --> 19:21.116
It's probably
for the best.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.292
No. I would have paid
to see that.

19:24.293 --> 19:25.425
Oh, yeah.

19:25.773 --> 19:26.730
So...

19:29.168 --> 19:30.343
This is for you.

19:32.954 --> 19:35.304
It's a moonshine
for new beginnings.

19:38.960 --> 19:39.787
Thank you.

19:40.875 --> 19:41.832
Yeah.

19:44.052 --> 19:46.489
I really admire

19:46.533 --> 19:48.883
your commitment
to making change

19:50.624 --> 19:55.411
and just your courage
to make a big personal one
to do it.

19:55.455 --> 19:57.587
And selfishly,
I wish you weren't leaving.

19:57.631 --> 19:58.936
[sniffles]

20:01.025 --> 20:02.418
And I'm really
gonna miss you.

20:04.594 --> 20:06.030
Thank you for everything.

20:07.989 --> 20:09.033
Come here.

20:10.600 --> 20:12.298
I'm gonna
miss you so much.

20:16.084 --> 20:19.000
Man, you really scored
the best loft
up on the roof, huh?

20:19.043 --> 20:21.872
Yeah, man, I,
uh, I lucked out.

20:21.916 --> 20:23.874
So when did you--
When did you move in
into The Coterie?

20:24.658 --> 20:25.485
Um...

20:28.183 --> 20:30.403
The first time
your moms came to visit,

20:30.446 --> 20:34.798
I told Stef about Jacob
before anyone else here knew.

20:34.842 --> 20:36.278
Oh, she never said anything.

20:36.322 --> 20:38.715
Yeah, I knew
she wouldn't.

20:38.759 --> 20:41.414
Somehow, I knew
I could trust her.

20:42.850 --> 20:43.938
That's an amazing thing.

20:45.287 --> 20:47.071
To have a family
that you can trust.

20:48.551 --> 20:51.424
You can carry that
anywhere you go.

20:51.467 --> 20:53.252
And that's how I know
you're gonna be okay.

20:57.430 --> 20:58.953
You're so amazing.

21:01.347 --> 21:02.173
Yeah.

21:02.870 --> 21:05.612
[loud laughter]

21:08.049 --> 21:10.312
GAEL:
How you doing?

21:10.356 --> 21:14.185
Uh... You know,
a lot of goodbyes.

21:16.275 --> 21:18.842
Yeah, well, you know
what they say.

21:18.886 --> 21:20.366
The nice thing
about goodbyes

21:20.409 --> 21:22.193
is it's just the chance
to say hello again.

21:23.282 --> 21:24.413
Where did you hear that?

21:25.762 --> 21:28.983
It's-- Maybe Mr. Rogers,
when I was a kid.

21:31.159 --> 21:32.378
[laughing] Yeah.

21:39.385 --> 21:41.430
We've had quite the journey
together.

21:43.998 --> 21:45.434
Hey, this isn't the end.

21:48.655 --> 21:51.658
Callie, you're someone
I want in my life forever.

21:55.966 --> 21:56.793
Ditto.

22:00.449 --> 22:04.105
♪

22:06.107 --> 22:07.108
To the UCLA!

22:07.151 --> 22:08.414
Uh, ACLU.

22:08.457 --> 22:09.415
That's what I said!

22:10.329 --> 22:12.896
♪ She's a crazy, crazy...

22:15.943 --> 22:18.337
This picture of Sandy Bullock
has always brought me good luck.

22:19.990 --> 22:21.514
Miss Congeniality herself.

22:24.081 --> 22:25.518
I'd like you to have it.

22:25.996 --> 22:28.477
Um... Wow!

22:29.435 --> 22:30.914
It's-- That's an honor.

22:30.958 --> 22:34.091
Um, are you sure
you want to part with it?

22:34.135 --> 22:36.529
It's not easy,
not gonna lie.

22:38.574 --> 22:40.228
But I wanted to give you
something that hurts.

22:42.317 --> 22:43.449
I hope that
when you look upon her,

22:44.580 --> 22:45.929
you'll think of me
and smile.

22:51.674 --> 22:53.154
I will. Thank you.

22:55.199 --> 22:56.418
Oh. Ahem.

23:03.382 --> 23:04.992
So how you really feeling,
Miss Thang?

23:05.775 --> 23:07.734
I feel fine!

23:07.777 --> 23:09.431
Has everyone forgotten
that I was the one

23:09.475 --> 23:10.432
that went away to college?

23:10.476 --> 23:12.391
Yeah, that's a good point.

23:12.434 --> 23:14.393
You have lived
away from us before.

23:14.436 --> 23:16.569
So why is everyone
so worried about me?

23:16.612 --> 23:17.657
Well, we're not just here

23:17.700 --> 23:19.180
because we're worried
about you.

23:19.223 --> 23:20.747
We're worried
about Callie too.

23:20.790 --> 23:23.445
You know,
she's always lived with
or near one of us.

23:23.489 --> 23:25.795
LENA: This is
a huge step for her.

23:25.839 --> 23:27.884
And I wonder,
maybe she was afraid
to tell you

23:27.928 --> 23:29.277
because once she did--

23:29.320 --> 23:30.931
STEF:
It made it real.

23:30.974 --> 23:33.586
["Body" by High Hoops playing]

23:33.629 --> 23:37.590
♪ I just wanna be the body
that you hang around ♪

23:39.330 --> 23:43.204
♪

23:44.640 --> 23:46.033
["Sensual" by TVA playing]

23:46.076 --> 23:50.820
♪ You got me runnin'
like a reject ♪

23:50.864 --> 23:53.475
I'm sorry that I dropped
the bomb at dinner, okay?

23:53.519 --> 23:56.304
You're such a dick sometimes.

23:56.347 --> 23:57.740
Yeah, I know.
I know.

23:59.786 --> 24:02.310
But I-- I did
take your advice
and called Carter.

24:02.353 --> 24:06.662
Mm-hmm. For less sexting,
more live video action?

24:06.706 --> 24:08.490
We compromised.

24:08.534 --> 24:09.622
A little of both.

24:09.665 --> 24:11.493
Okay.
Not in my loft, right?

24:11.537 --> 24:13.539
Ugh, Ka'Maya's in there
sleeping!

24:13.974 --> 24:14.931
Jeez.

24:18.239 --> 24:19.370
So...

24:20.459 --> 24:23.200
are you okay
with me leaving?

24:25.115 --> 24:25.942
Yeah.

24:26.856 --> 24:28.815
I-- I-- I told you,

24:28.858 --> 24:31.252
now I have two reasons
to go back East to visit.

24:31.295 --> 24:32.819
And you're welcome any time.

24:36.997 --> 24:38.433
I love you.

24:39.216 --> 24:39.826
I love you too.

24:41.741 --> 24:42.959
Give me a hug.

24:43.003 --> 24:44.526
Come on.

24:44.570 --> 24:46.136
♪ Run through your heart

24:46.180 --> 24:47.747
♪ I'm running
through your heart ♪

24:47.790 --> 24:49.662
♪ Yeah, right through
your heart ♪

24:52.360 --> 24:53.666
She's so sweet.

24:54.144 --> 24:56.233
Hmm, she is.

24:56.277 --> 24:59.062
Hey, why were you so afraid
to leave her tonight?

25:02.109 --> 25:05.286
I feel guilty about
how much I'm away for work.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.507
I mean, I know
my job is important.

25:10.117 --> 25:13.512
But it is really hard
being away from both of you.

25:14.338 --> 25:15.775
I'm missing so much.

25:15.818 --> 25:16.732
How'd-- How did I
not even know

25:16.776 --> 25:17.951
she doesn't like
peanut butter?

25:19.822 --> 25:21.345
I thought parenting
was supposed to be...

25:22.521 --> 25:24.697
easier the second time around.

25:28.352 --> 25:31.094
I realize how lucky I am

25:31.138 --> 25:33.793
to be able to spend so much time
at home with Ka'Maya.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.492
But knowing whether
she likes peanut butter or not

25:37.536 --> 25:40.060
is not a measure
of how bonded you are to her.

25:40.103 --> 25:43.716
You are an amazing mother,
Lena, and she adores you.

25:48.938 --> 25:52.246
I wish all of our kids
were little again.

25:55.554 --> 25:57.817
I cannot believe
that Callie is moving
so far away.

25:59.296 --> 26:00.820
And Jesus in India,

26:00.863 --> 26:03.431
with Emma, Brandon,
and Eliza in Europe.

26:03.474 --> 26:07.696
I mean, they're scattered
to the wind, those guys.

26:07.740 --> 26:09.611
I don't know how much more
my heart can take.

26:15.878 --> 26:17.924
I guess parenting is...

26:19.882 --> 26:21.928
the daily process
of letting go.

26:25.366 --> 26:26.149
Come here.

26:34.027 --> 26:36.812
♪

26:43.602 --> 26:46.474
-[glass clinking]
-Okay. Guys, speech time.

26:55.526 --> 26:58.834
Hmm, I'm gonna try
and get through this
without crying. Um...

27:01.837 --> 27:04.405
Thank you for this
impromptu going-away party.

27:05.145 --> 27:05.754
Um...

27:07.756 --> 27:11.020
As some of you may know,
I had no idea

27:11.064 --> 27:14.850
that I was moving
into a communal living space.

27:16.417 --> 27:21.335
Um... after sharing a bathroom
with four siblings,

27:21.378 --> 27:24.686
the idea of sharing one
with a dozen strangers

27:24.730 --> 27:27.820
just sounded like a nightmare.
[laughs]

27:31.954 --> 27:34.261
But I had no idea
how lucky I was

27:34.304 --> 27:37.394
that my sister tricked me
into moving in here.

27:38.961 --> 27:43.052
Um, you know,
when you leave the family

27:43.096 --> 27:47.666
that you were born into,
or adopted into,

27:48.797 --> 27:49.972
you go out in the world,

27:50.016 --> 27:53.454
you get to make
a chosen family...

27:54.498 --> 27:55.499
of friends.

27:59.025 --> 28:01.897
And I will never find
a better-chosen family
than you guys.

28:03.899 --> 28:05.509
Really.

28:05.553 --> 28:07.598
I just--
I love you all so much.

28:09.862 --> 28:10.906
And, um...

28:13.953 --> 28:17.957
Thank you for letting me
be a part of The Coterie.

28:20.481 --> 28:21.612
We love you.

28:24.964 --> 28:26.530
["Party Rock Anthem"
by LMFAO playing]

28:26.574 --> 28:29.969
[all cheering]

28:33.799 --> 28:35.235
♪ Let's go

28:35.278 --> 28:38.673
♪ Party rock
is in the house tonight ♪

28:38.717 --> 28:40.457
♪ We just wanna see you

28:42.503 --> 28:43.417
♪ Shake that!

28:47.029 --> 28:49.075
♪

28:51.164 --> 28:54.602
♪ Party rock
is in the house tonight ♪

28:54.645 --> 28:57.692
♪ Everybody just have
a good time ♪

28:57.736 --> 28:59.128
♪ I can feel it, baby!

28:59.172 --> 29:02.479
♪ And we gonna make you
lose your mind ♪

29:02.523 --> 29:07.180
♪ Everybody just have
a good, good, good time ♪

29:07.223 --> 29:11.097
♪ Ooohh! Ooooh!
Put your hands up ♪

29:11.140 --> 29:13.186
♪ Ooohh! Ooooh!
Put your hands up ♪

29:13.229 --> 29:14.709
♪ Shake that!

29:14.753 --> 29:16.711
♪ Every day I'm shuf-f-f-ling

29:22.630 --> 29:23.849
MARIANA:
So...

29:24.632 --> 29:25.764
Moms sext?

29:26.199 --> 29:27.766
Yeah.

29:27.809 --> 29:30.507
Yeah, that was more than
I needed to know.

29:37.340 --> 29:38.167
So.

29:39.734 --> 29:40.561
So.

29:42.389 --> 29:43.303
So enough about me.

29:44.304 --> 29:45.435
How do you feel
about going?

29:50.049 --> 29:50.876
Scared.

29:54.967 --> 29:57.099
Um, I've never really
been on my own

29:57.143 --> 30:00.320
since Jude and I
became Adams-Fosters.

30:03.714 --> 30:05.586
I just feel like
I need to find myself

30:06.587 --> 30:07.893
and my purpose.

30:13.420 --> 30:14.682
[tearfully]:
I just wish it didn't mean

30:14.725 --> 30:16.205
moving away from you,
you know?

30:22.603 --> 30:24.257
What if I screw it up?

30:26.041 --> 30:27.216
What if I fail?

30:29.784 --> 30:31.830
What if I...

30:31.873 --> 30:34.354
come crawling back here
with my tail between my legs?

30:37.226 --> 30:40.839
Then you will be welcomed
with open arms.

30:42.579 --> 30:45.844
You're not
gonna fail, Callie.

30:45.887 --> 30:48.194
You're the most
exceptional person
that I know.

30:49.673 --> 30:51.284
And once you find
your purpose in life,

30:52.720 --> 30:54.287
there's gonna be
no stopping you.

30:56.071 --> 30:57.507
You're ready
to leave home.

30:59.553 --> 31:02.643
And you'll never be
on your own completely.

31:04.166 --> 31:05.907
Our family will always
be there for you,

31:05.951 --> 31:08.301
both Adams-Fosters
and The Coterie.

31:10.564 --> 31:11.608
And you know
what they say.

31:13.567 --> 31:16.352
Geography doesn't make
a family, love does.

31:17.310 --> 31:19.312
Who says that?

31:19.355 --> 31:22.402
Me. Based on something
Mama once told me.

31:22.445 --> 31:26.449
♪

31:26.493 --> 31:28.190
STEF: Looks like
someone could use
a momma sandwich.

31:28.234 --> 31:29.496
What do you say?

31:35.676 --> 31:37.721
Oh, my babies.

31:38.809 --> 31:40.159
My babies.

31:40.202 --> 31:41.943
Speaking
of sandwiches...

31:41.987 --> 31:43.945
My babies. Hi!

31:43.989 --> 31:45.686
You remember when Callie
stole a sandwich

31:45.729 --> 31:46.948
and got sent to juvie?

31:46.992 --> 31:48.689
Always with
the sandwich story!

31:49.255 --> 31:50.996
Always!

31:51.039 --> 31:53.824
Okay, how about
when Mariana pierced
her own nose?

31:54.347 --> 31:55.565
That was cute.

31:55.609 --> 31:57.350
How about when you, uh,
dyed your hair blonde?

31:57.393 --> 32:00.353
Oh, this coming from a girl
who got into a car with a pimp?

32:00.396 --> 32:01.963
Okay.
All right.

32:02.007 --> 32:03.965
Happy memories only.

32:11.364 --> 32:14.889
♪

32:23.071 --> 32:25.726
♪

32:49.489 --> 32:53.928
[phone vibrating]

32:57.671 --> 32:59.194
Hey, Mom.

32:59.238 --> 33:00.500
WOMAN:
We need to talk
about your sister.

33:00.543 --> 33:02.023
Why? What about her?

33:02.067 --> 33:03.198
WOMAN:
I've never
told your father this

33:03.242 --> 33:04.199
because it would upset him,

33:04.243 --> 33:06.027
but after Jenna left home,

33:06.071 --> 33:09.117
every year on my birthday,
she would send me a postcard.

33:09.161 --> 33:10.901
JOAQUIN:
Why wouldn't you tell me?

33:10.945 --> 33:13.121
This whole time,
I thought no one's heard
from her in eight years.

33:13.165 --> 33:15.515
WOMAN:
The point is, I didn't get
a postcard from her this year,

33:15.558 --> 33:16.951
and my birthday
was six months ago.

33:16.995 --> 33:18.474
Do you have any idea
where she is?

33:22.565 --> 33:25.742
["Morning Sun"
by Jordan Max playing]

33:25.786 --> 33:28.267
WOMAN:
The last postcard she sent me
had a return address

33:28.310 --> 33:30.573
from someplace
called The Coterie
at the Palace Theater.

33:31.922 --> 33:33.707
♪ Lost in your tradition

33:33.750 --> 33:35.056
♪ Stronger than addiction

33:35.100 --> 33:36.971
♪ Out of control

33:39.234 --> 33:40.366
♪ We've all been conditioned

33:40.409 --> 33:41.932
♪ Follow your religion

33:41.976 --> 33:43.717
♪ Don't sell your soul

33:45.545 --> 33:47.155
♪ Dreams and premonitions

33:47.199 --> 33:48.896
♪ Use my intuition

33:48.939 --> 33:50.767
♪ Before the storms

33:50.811 --> 33:52.552
WOMAN:
You don't think it's some
kind of cult, do you?

33:52.595 --> 33:55.381
When she left home
and rejected God
and the church,

33:55.424 --> 33:58.601
she was inviting in
the influence of demons.

33:58.645 --> 34:00.777
JOAQUIN:
Mom, I'm sure she's fine.

34:00.821 --> 34:03.606
WOMAN:
Then why didn't I get
a postcard this year?

34:03.650 --> 34:05.869
What if something horrible
has happened to her?

34:05.913 --> 34:07.828
Oh, please, pray with me.

34:09.743 --> 34:11.658
Our Father in heaven,

34:11.701 --> 34:15.618
hallowed be your name,
your kingdom come,

34:15.662 --> 34:18.143
your will be done,
on Earth as it is in heaven.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.625
♪

34:24.497 --> 34:27.500
♪ Lord, give me your light

34:27.543 --> 34:30.807
♪ Rise like my time has come

34:30.851 --> 34:34.159
♪ Lord, make me aright

34:34.202 --> 34:35.986
♪ Devils keep calling

34:36.030 --> 34:38.206
♪ Is our world falling down?

34:44.430 --> 34:47.694
♪ Lord, make me aright

34:53.178 --> 34:55.136
CALLIE: So, uh,
I just want to point out

34:55.180 --> 34:59.271
that this here is what
the yellow zone is for...

34:59.314 --> 35:00.533
loading and unloading.

35:01.795 --> 35:03.492
I can't believe
our U-Haul got towed

35:03.536 --> 35:05.451
and robbed
the first day we got here.

35:07.801 --> 35:09.237
Where'd you get that?

35:10.064 --> 35:11.413
Um...

35:14.329 --> 35:16.897
Um, is everything okay?

35:16.940 --> 35:19.334
Yeah. I just-- Um...

35:19.378 --> 35:22.424
I haven't told Mariana yet
that I'm leaving, so...

35:22.468 --> 35:25.819
Ah, well,
I won't keep you then.

35:25.862 --> 35:27.908
I just wasn't sure
when you were going,

35:27.951 --> 35:30.998
and I wanted
to give you this.

35:36.612 --> 35:40.225
My mother gave that to me
when I graduated law school.

35:43.619 --> 35:47.536
And I always thought
that if I ever had
a daughter,

35:47.580 --> 35:50.148
I would want
to hand it down to her.

35:56.589 --> 35:57.677
It's beautiful.

36:01.942 --> 36:03.117
Thank you, Kathleen.

36:04.640 --> 36:05.511
So much.

36:06.381 --> 36:07.208
For this.

36:08.862 --> 36:09.689
For everything.

36:12.474 --> 36:14.128
Yeah. Well, I'm not a hugger.

36:15.303 --> 36:16.870
-That's okay.
-Okay.

36:16.913 --> 36:18.088
It's fine.

36:20.526 --> 36:21.788
Go get 'em, kid.

36:27.489 --> 36:29.578
-Well, that was sweet of her.
-Yeah, it was.

36:33.321 --> 36:35.280
[clears throat]
Okay.

36:36.542 --> 36:38.718
This is it.

36:38.761 --> 36:42.983
Well, almost all of it.

36:43.026 --> 36:44.898
Don't open it till you get
on the plane, okay?

36:44.941 --> 36:46.726
["It's Okay"
by Nightbirde playing]

36:50.991 --> 36:55.691
♪ I changed my name thinking
that it would change my mind ♪

36:55.735 --> 36:57.389
I'll, um, I'll call you
from the airport.

36:57.432 --> 36:59.260
-And when you land.
-Of course.

36:59.304 --> 37:00.870
♪ I thought
that all my problems ♪

37:00.914 --> 37:02.872
